					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, that works OK too, for less targets.  But you still have to poll it the same way, during the frame rendering and during all the scanlines you want to check (it won't "remember" hitting it if you wait too long to read it).  So there really is no way to avoid using some sort of timed code.  From there it's pretty easy to increment a timer in that loop, and use it if it's useful (even if it's not exactly scanline-timed).</div>

