					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">1. Mostly because you typically wouldn't want to overflow the frame time - you're gonna have to know how long you'll be polling it for.  So it doesn't have to be 100% exact, but you will want to know (at least roughly) how much CPU time, and how many scanlines, are being spent.
<br />
<br />2. I wondered about that, I didn't try it though.  But on the zapper test I did, it seemed like moving the gun horizontally was having no effect (but my code wasn't made to test H movement specifically).  Not sure I trust the emulators on stuff like this (stuff that no game probably ever did).</div>

